The convert-unixlib.pl script in this directory can be used
to convert the standard AOF-style UnixLib structure into a build
system suitable for ELF.  This includes converting the assembler files
into ELF-syntax suitable for compiling with GAS.

To perform the task, just type:

$ convert-unixlib.pl gccsdk-3.4/unixlib dest_dir/unixlib

Then to build unixlib you do this:

$ cd dest_dir/unixlib
$ mkdir arm-riscos
$ cd arm-riscos
$ CC=arm-riscos-elf-gcc OBJCOPY=arm-riscos-elf-objcopy ../configure --prefix=/home/riscos/env/unixlib
$ make
$ make install


Nothing in this directory should be distributed outside of
the GCCSDK source tree.
